Olive Oil
½ onion
1 parsnip
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
½ lemon
1 bunch spring onion
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 tsp brown sugar
¼ tsp salt
1 packet chicken breast
20 g butter
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 clove garlic
1 sachet Berbere seasoning
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
Slice the red onion (see ingredients) into thick
wedges. Cut the parsnip into small chunks. Place
the peeled & chopped pumpkin, onion and
parsnip on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil
and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and
roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: If your oven tray looks crowded, separate the
veggies across two oven trays!

While the veggies are roasting, finely chop the
garlic. Zest the lemon to get a pinch, then slice in
half. Thinly slice the spring onion. Roughly chop
the baby spinach leaves. In a large bowl, combine
the Berbere seasoning, brown sugar, the salt,
a good squeeze of lemon juice and a generous
drizzle of olive oil. Add the chicken breast and
turn to coat. Set aside.

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, cook the chicken until golden,
2-3 minutes each side. Transfer the chicken to
a second lined oven tray and bake until cooked
through, 8-12 minutes. Set the chicken aside to
rest for 5 minutes.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, melt the butter in a
medium saucepan over a medium-high heat. Cook
the garlic until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the water
and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the
boil. Add the couscous and stir to combine, then
cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set
aside until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes.
Fluff up with a fork. Add the roasted veggies, baby
spinach, lemon zest and spring onion (reserve a
little for garnish) and stir to combine. Season
to taste.

In a small bowl, combine the Greek-style yoghurt
and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste.

Slice the Berbere chicken. Divide the roast veggie
couscous between plates and top with the chicken,
spooning any resting juices over the chicken.
Drizzle with the lemon yoghurt and garnish with
the reserved spring onion.